Notes: READNFO - NEW VIDEO SOURCE which means there aren't blackouts constantly, there is nowhere near as much
camera movement and the quality is a little better.

Now, it's been seriously years since we've done this much work on a CAM. We're going to try and keep this as
short and to the point as possible. Firstly we had to sync the audio from the previous CAM (yes same audio
until something better appears), had to make a good 7-8 cuts in order to sync the audio, it was pretty damn
hard to in the dark scenes. Then came the problem of the watermarks, the video has spanish watermarks on around
6-7 parts in the video, we cut the video up once again and then placed a blur over the watermarks in the 6-7 spots
where they did occur, this makes it easier to view and also makes it site friendly. The watermarked blurs last
for a grand total of 5 minutes or so throughout the movie so they're nothing major at all really. Once that was
done we stiched all of the video pieces back together and got down to filtering, adjusted the colours and did
some cropping of the borders and then here we have it. File size came out a little bit smaller than we had
hoped so we may do a 1.4gb version tomorrow if nobody has one out by then. Russian video lasted around 1h 50mn,
this is only 1h 48mn due to the cuts that were made throughout for watermarks and audio syncing. We did this
only because nobody currently has and to shut the people up that said the last Godzilla source was watchable
if it wasn't for all of the movement and blackouts, well this doesn't have that so here you go.



